{"_id":"plcjPDrKKteVGMxM","name":"The Alchemist","permission":{"default":0,"ZhC8ATjW2zJWoMct":3},"type":"class","data":{"name":"","description":"<h2>The Alchemist</h2>\n<p>Other people might know how to shoot fireballs from their fingertips, or slice a man in half, lengthwise, or the right way to jostle that mechanism so you&rsquo;re not crushed to death by some deathtrap left by maniacs miles underground. That&rsquo;s fine. Those people have their uses.</p>\n<p>But you, Alchemist, know something they don&rsquo;t. Lots of things, probably, but one thing very important. You know that a change is coming. You know that there will be a time when it&rsquo;s not might, not magic, not monsters that rule Dungeon World. You know.</p>\n<p>You know, because you carry the future with you wherever you go. One day, when you&rsquo;ve catalogued the known effects of this and that reagent, when you&rsquo;ve sussed out the phlogistons from the oxygens, when you&rsquo;ve learned all there is to learn, when that day comes, it will be you, at the forefront, leading the way into a gleaming, glorious world of truth, of beauty, of scientific progress.</p>\n<p>If only they hadn&rsquo;t buried all those secrets deep down below the earth. Bottle those plans, Alchemist. They&rsquo;ll be worth their weight in gold one day.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Names</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Human: Hermes, Albertus, Ramon, Lille, Simone, Ostanes, Nicolas, Mary</li>\n<li>Gnome: Fizzlecup, Bubbledob, Lemons, Quirk, Zimmerzag, Cary, Pumpkin</li>\n<li>Elf: Agathodae, Lasgale, Eowyr, Telenwe, Nandori, Amrothin, Uwon, Celegin</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Look</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>CLOTHES: Stained, Heavy-duty, Gold-embroidered, or _ ___________</li>\n<li>EYES: Melty, Manic, Bright, or _ ___________</li>\n<li>HAIR: Greasy, Singed, Hat, or _ ___________</li>\n<li>HANDS: Dirty, Burnt, Gloved, or _ ___________</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Bonds</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>I have a l ot of work to do, teaching _____________ how the world really works.</li>\n<li>______________ i s a great test subject! I should get them i nvolved in my work.</li>\n<li>______________ i s almost as volatile as some of my reagents! We don&rsquo;t mix well.</li>\n<li>I have a l ot of respect for _____________, and their hard won knowledge. Maybe I can get them to teach me.</li>\n<li>I&rsquo;m not sure I trust _____________ with my potions or secrets.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Gear</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>You know that i t matters to start with the right i ngredients:</li>\n<li>Your Formula Book ( 1 weight) and basic Lab Materials (1 weight)</li>\n<li>Alchemical Reagents ( 6 uses, 0 weight), Uses l eft: 6 An owlbear&rsquo;s ear, some fungus, weird l iquids - anything vaguely i nteresting, and more can always be found.</li>\n<li>Leather Armor ( 1 armor, worn, 1 weight)</li>\n<li>Dungeon Rations ( 5 uses, r ation, 1 weight), Uses l eft: 5</li>\n<li>9 Coins</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Choose up to two:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Mace ( close, 1 weight)</li>\n<li>Dagger ( hand, 1 weight)</li>\n<li>Ragged bow ( near, 2 weight) and Bundle of arrows ( 3 ammo, 1 weight), Ammo l eft: 3</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Choose one more:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Two healing potions ( 0 weight),</li>\n<li>Adventuring gear ( 5 uses, 1 weight), Uses l eft: 5 &amp; Antitoxin ( 0 weight)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>About The Alchemist</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Formula Book.\n<ul>\n<li>The Alchemist starts level 1 with three kinds of experiments: Healing potions and two others of their choice.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>In The Mix<br />\n<ul>\n<li>The intention of this move is to let the Alchemist get a little creative within the bounds of their experiments. When they want to make something alchemical happen, this is the move they should roll, with one exception - if it&rsquo;s an attack/throwing a vial, it&rsquo;s probably a Volley (unless the target is close enough to easily hit), and their attack gains the appropriate tags. Rolling+INT is meant to signal creativity/planning/intention in a way beyond &ldquo;I throw to hit them&rdquo;. For that reason, it&rsquo;s possible to do some weird things - does an electrochemical healing experiment zap people to heal them? Does an endothermic plant grow icicles or does it grow a big snowman? All of these results are acceptable to me, but the GM gets final say. Importantly, nearly each kind of experiment is d angerous.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Gather Reagents<br />\n<ul>\n<li>This move guarantees that the Alchemist will get reagents when they go out looking, without a roll. It does not protect them from the dangers of being in a place where alchemical materials can be found - those dangers might still need to be defied, for example.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Homebrewing&nbsp;\n<ul>\n<li>If the Alchemist wants to do something not covered by In The Mix, they can always turn to homebrewing. This move mimics the Wizard&rsquo;s Ritual, and can do just about anything (as long as the conditions are met).</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Polyjuice Potion, Roguelike, and Hops, Barley, and Everything Gnarly\n<ul>\n<li>These moves have fairly straightforward effects on their own, but also add complexity and options to In The Mix - again, what a poisonous combustion experiment does is open to interpretation.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Mixomancer and Chemistry Wizard<br />\n<ul>\n<li>These moves make individual spells replicable with In The Mix, but always require special material components to use - something more than just standard alchemical reagents.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Biovisionary<br />\n<ul>\n<li>Like all ritual-like effects, this requires a little more input from the player, and exactly how to bottle life essence to create life in the lab is something the GM will need to provide input on.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Potionblood<br />\n<ul>\n<li>Picking up this move means that the Alchemist can exude liquids now! It&rsquo;s just a thing they can do. It might be through their palms, or maybe their spit or even their blood. There&rsquo;s some fuzziness as to whether the bonus and penalty are part of the effects of the alchemical substance (and thus transferrable) or unique to the Alchemist&rsquo;s particular biochemistry. This particular implementation is left up to the conversation between the Alchemist and the GM. Two reminders - First, that GM characters don&rsquo;t have stats, so any effect there will be up to the GM&rsquo;s discretion. Second, that other Powered by the Apocalypse games often cap the final modifier to a roll at +4, since beyond that it is impossible to roll a 6-.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>","races":{"0":{"label":"Human","description":"When you l ook for rare reagents in a new land, ask the GM what rare materials can be found here. They’ll tell you, but it’s up to you to find them."},"1":{"label":"Gnome","description":"When you e nter civilized society, you can find someone to honor the tinker’s tradition. Tell the GM what you have to barter and they’ll give you an offer. Take i t or don’t."},"2":{"label":"Elf","description":"When you a ccentuate your senses with alchemical materials, mark off one alchemical reagent, and your senses are attuned to magic as though you had cast Detect Magic"},"3":{"label":"???","description":""}},"alignments":{"0":{"label":"Good","description":"Directly aid another with your knowledge or skill."},"1":{"label":"Neutral","description":"Endanger yourself i n the name of i nquiry."},"2":{"label":"Chaotic","description":"Break the barriers that keep you from progress."},"3":{"label":"???","description":""}},"equipment":{"0":{"label":"You know that i t matters to start with the right i ngredients:","mode":"checkbox","items":["EC2nlpHL7DeosJ5A","KzwSbDftiTcjelfE","20BjUYQNJ8X5dzds"]},"1":{"label":"Choose up to two:","mode":"checkbox","items":["LmjG7mONJ7GIBHIc","jSFKrGehEa3y26cO","nMag6sXXRqc6SC4Q","WrnuJ6j8JerAozDO"]},"2":{"label":"Choose one more:","mode":"checkbox","items":["YwHV7WYzTPSAOorl","CMhNmAwhLVZk9lfq","4rXRNHipSXLO6pnP"